Silk frauds on a Halong Bay cruise
Jul 2014 ‚Ä¢ Solo
I booked a one day Halong Bay cruise in July, the tour operator was South Pacific Travel. On our way to Halon Bay we stopped at "ABC" shopping center/restaurant in Dong Trieu, Quang Ninh. I bought three ladies kimonoes which by the sales person
were 100% silk. There were also big signs advertising sales items to be "silk". The kimonoes have also labels 100% silk. While another sales assistant was wrapping them up, I was taken on a tour around the shop. So it was only in the evening when back in the hotel I discovered those gowns were fakes, 100% polyester.
I contacted the shop but they insisted those gowns are indeed 100% vietnamese silk. And of course they refused to refund $100 I paid. I suggested I would send those fakes back so that they could replace them with real silk but was told they will not replace used items. Well, I haven't used them and I never will.
As for the cruise: even though it was low season the bay and the cave were overcowded. Lunch was served but the quality of vegetarian choise was poor. Boat was not as luxury as in pictures and the ladders which were used to climb on/off the boat were shaky and dangerous.
The whole tour was a huge disappointment. In my opinion there is no reason to to Halong Bay, especially if you have been to Krabi, Thailand. The scenery very much alike.
Written September 17, 2014
