Princess Junk, Halong Bay
Mar 2014 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We spent a lovely night on a private junk in Halong Bay, unfortunately the weather didn't cooperate, but the service provided by the Princess Junk crew more than made up for it. The gorgeous dark wood cabin was romantic and had an ensuite bathroom complete with nice shower. We spent as much time on the deck as possible but it was chilly, the crew were more than accommodating at providing blankets to make us comfortable. The meals were to die for! Mostly 6 courses, lots of fresh seafood, and all presented as a piece of art. We were able to do a little kayaking, visited a cave, and saw a floating village, all in the rain, but again our guide, and the staff were all very up beat and it made for a great experience. I would love to go back one day, and I would definitely go with Princess Junk!
