Susan Neilson
New Canaan, CT5 contributions
Pearl Factory
Mar 2014 ‚Ä¢ Friends
Our guide on a Ha Long Bay cruise arranged by our ship Regent Seven Seas Voyager told us about the pearl business in this area. We wanted to go to the pearl farms but that was more than 3 hours away. At our request though he arranged a taxi to take us to one of the pearl factories nearby -Viet Hung Pearl Plaza. We quibbled on the fare - he wanted $80 we agreed to $28, $7 each for the 4 ladies who wanted to go. The taxi arrived on time at the pier after lunch. Viet Hung Pearl Plaza is just on the outskirts of Ha Long. A modern, immaculate building with several attractive showrooms selling pearls and and products. Lots of Pearl jewelry was display attractively. We were welcomed by several of the sales staff. Each salesperson had a couple of young women who assisted in the sales process- holding your coat, putting on the pearls, holding the mirror, etc. We all bought something after negotiating. The 2 main salesmen, Rick and John, spoke excellent English, were very cordial and professional but had a good sense of humor about the negotiating. I did not intend to look for pearls in Vietnam but believe I purchased a lovely strand of 13mm multi color pastel pearls with a magnificent luster Nancy Pelosi would wear them I'm sure. I will have the necklace appraised to confirm my purchase. This business does not have a website listed on its brochure, so it doesnt't qualify for its own listing on TripAdvisor. I wanted to get the name out their so am reviewing it under Ha Long Bay itself. Address is DC: Khu 3. (Cho Vuon Dao) - TP, Ha Long - Quang Ninh, Vietnam. telephone is 0333.511.366. Fax: 0333.511.689. Gave the brochure to Desination Services on Regent. Hope they add this shop to a tour.
Written March 9, 2014
namalada
New York City, NY18 contributions
Halong Dragon Cruise (deluxe) - 2day, 1night with APT travel
Dec 2013 ‚Ä¢ Solo
This tour was booked for me by the sales agent at my hotel (TIME HOTEL in Hanoi). Ms Anna was insisting that i book 2 day instead of 1 day. i didn't need much convincing actually. And in the end i wish i could've done 3 days! so thank yo miss anna :-)
i think i lucked out. the whole experience was fantastic.
i was picked up at the hotel at 830am (they picked me up last :-)) and then we were off on about 3hr bus ride to Halong Bay. It passed quite fast. With a 30min stop at some store to allow us to buy souvenirs. Although this may seem like an inconvenience to us, it's a necessity for the drivers to have a break, eat something and use the facilities. Us too i guess. The guide was very funny and nice. Duk or Daniel as he asked us to call him. But then he explained to me that I wouldn't be in his group :-(. since i was doing a 2 day tour i would be transferred to a different group when we arrived at Halong Bay. Bummer. I thought he was so funny.
It was a little chaotic when we arrived at the ferry terminal. so many tourists getting bussed there. don't be alarmed. the bay is big enough to handle all of you. Daniel took me to a guy wearing an interesting hat (a green hard safari hat!) and said, stay with him. this is the captain of your boat. the captain motioned to me to stay put and went off somewhere. i was a little panicked but i didn't need to be. Daniel came back to get me and introduced me to my new tour guide and group. whew. and we were off.
took small speed boats from Ferry to our Cruise. the Cruise itself looks unimpressive from the outside but is great inside. beautiful maintained in the guest area. lovely crew of young Vietnamese guys (i felt bad when i found out they were away from their families for long periods while they worked on the boats). i lucked out and got a private (i had requested a double with any other female...but since there wasn't one to match up with me i got the fab single). they also provide me with a gorgeous plate of fresh fruit (i thought everyone got it!). MMMMM. the food on the boat was fabulous. we were provided lunch and dinner on first day and breakfast and lunch on second day. the group on the boat was a quieter crowd. it fit me perfectly. as the single traveller i was put at the table with a family from Indonesia. they were sooo lovely. the upper deck was fabulous. in warm weather i can see how this would be amazing. even in the cold i loved it.
our activities were packed in day 1. but i was glad for it. because next day we were able to really take it easy. we visited the caves (with hoards of other tourists...maybe doing this first thing on day 2 would be better), then hiked to top of t-top mt. fabulous views. saw the beginnings of the sunset. well worth the 400+ steps in my opinion. and finally kayaked in a luon cave. all good.
second day woke up and watched sunrise and enjoyed the leisurely cruise around the bay. we were all saying how fabulous this whole experience was and that we'd have loved to stay another day. after breakfast (which was my least favorite meal because it was eggs and toast) we visited a pearl farm and then started to head back to port.
we had a bit of a wait for our bus to arrive (traffic). but there was a nearby restaurant where we were all able to hang out and chat while we waited. Miss Anna had arranged for them to drop me off on the way to Hanoi so that I could take a cab direct to the airport. I was flying out at 8pm that day. they dropped me off around 4pm and so i made it with plenty of time.
i highly recommend this tour company. APT travel and the Halong Dragon Cruise. As i mention i did the deluxe tour. they also have superior tour (i'm not sure the difference). I paid 95USD for the 2 day/1night trip.
Written January 7, 2014
